This paper deals with reinforcement learning and human interaction, which are both core topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for reward prediction also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on human-centered design and user feedback, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of models for forward dynamics and safety also suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
